					 In this article 
						 Note Azure has two different deployment models for creating and working with resources:   Resource Manager and classic . This article covers using both models, but Microsoft recommends that most new deployments use the Resource Manager model. 
 
 Summary: 
 Determining which application pattern or patterns to use for your SQL-Server-based applications in Azure environment is an important design decision and it requires a solid understanding of how SQL Server and each infrastructure component of Azure 